  <br>
  I'm curious to know how Renux's resists are to rogue poison. Our guild doesn't have a level 58+ druid that can aid in the Renux battle, so I'm having to come up with some possible impromptu strategies if we can't find a high-level druid outside our guild to help us.<br>
<br>
  My first question is, can Rangers and Druids snare equally well?  Perhaps if I can't find a high enough level druid, I can look for a high enough level ranger to fulfill the task. I assume that they both have the same snaring abilities and that the main  reason for the druid to snare is to maintain argo by casting multiple DoT's, etc.  If this is the case, I plan on using a ranger to snare, and a high-level wizard to take the punishment, this way, if the snare wears off, our snarer won't be killed.<br>
<br>
  My second question is, if I cannot find either to help me, how does Renux stand up against rogue poison?  I've heard that the general is an easy target for rogue poisons.  Could it be possible for me to use a simple basalisk poison (muscle lock) and use that for a snare on Renux?  How does the level 1 muscle lock poison compare with a regular snare? I know the duration is much longer, but will it slow the opponent as slow or even slower?  In this case, then perhaps the best way to snare kite Renux is with rogue poisons.  I would love to test this theory, but in the same regard, I do NOT want to have to jeopardize my epic progress on an unproven theory.<br>
<br>
  But if it does work, then maybe it's a much better solution (assuming the rogue doesn't mind tanking one round of Renux attacks and a possible clockwork stun =\).<br>
<br>
Thank you all for the help!<br>
<br>
Talas - 54 rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalasdruzzilro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talas DruzzilRo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/01 7:12:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux vs. Rogue Poison</span><hr size=1> &lt;bumping it up, just in case some missed it&gt;<br>
<br>
So no one's used poison on Renux?  I made some Basilisk poison to aid in the raid on Tuesday (muscle lock I - snare 31-40%; 6 seconds/level) and was wondering if this will be effective.  I've looked around more for Renux's resists v. poison and still have turned up dry.  Has anyone used poison on Renux?  If so, which kind, and did it have a successfull roll?  Thanks.<br>
<br>
Talas <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallusgrimblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kallus Grimblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/01 8:48:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> From my experience....</span><hr size=1> When I did renux, it was with a 55 ranger (love ya still glem). The thing is, she tried a lot of snares and I mean a lot, none of them landed until we got a chanter to come by and tash her. As for poisons, I have no clue on what her resists are. So basically, if you have a chanter to tash her, than yes, there is no difference in ranger and druid snaring. Btw, I wouldn't suggest the wizard/druid combo unless theres a enchanter or the wizard uses pure flame lures. Worst comes to worst if you wanna do it without renux snared, it is very well possible. Before the chanter came to help, I was able to effectively kite her around the windmill (with just sow) area down to approx. 70 percent. In the end, chanter came by tashed, Ranger snared, pets ate renux alive =)<br>
<br>
Kallus Grimblade<br>
Blackguard of the 59th Season<br>
&quot;How often is it that you've had a women hand you your heart Kallus!&quot;<br>
         -Renux Herkanor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kirna>Kirna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/15/01 11:52:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: From my experience....</span><hr size=1> It's been many months since I did her, but when we did her a 52 druid snared her no problem (about 9 in 10 success rate).  We did however have a mage and enchanter, so Renux had tash/mal on.  We had no problem fear-kiting Renux at the time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3073.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3068.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3060.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3060.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3060.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3060.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form 